This is a simple Flask MVP app.

## Structure
- app.py: main entry point, routes and server setup
- config.py: configuration variables
- models/: business logic
- db/: database file storage (csv, json, sqlite, etc.)
- templates/: HTML (Jinja2)
- static/: CSS, JS, images

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Python + Flask
- Templating: Jinja2
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (CDN, no npm)

## Tailwind Usage
- Load Tailwind via CDN in base template
- Use utility classes directly in HTML
- Do not set up a Tailwind build pipeline or npm

## Guidelines
- Separate concerns clearly:
  - Routes in app.py
  - Logic in models/

## When Adding Features
- Reuse existing structure(even existing funcitons)
- Prefer simple solutions over clever ones
